
<% priority 10 %>

<% if details['urls'].size >1 %>
<% name "Unvalidated Redirect [#{details['urls'].size} urls]" %>
<% else %>
<% name "Unvalidated Redirect [1 url]" %>
<% end %>

<b>Description:</b> Unvalidated redirects have been found. Attacker could link to unvalidated redirect and trick victims into clicking it. <br/>
<b>Affected URLs:</b><br/>


<% details['urls'].each_pair do |url, method| %>

<%= "#{method}" %> request for <%= "#{url}<br/>" %>

<% end %>

<b>Remediation:</b> Try not to use redirects. If used, do not involve user parameters.<br/>
<b>References:</b></br> 
OWASP - https://www.owasp.org/index.php/Top_10_2013-A10-Unvalidated_Redirects_and_Forwards<br/>

